CPU (Processor)

*What a CPU does?
- CPU is the brain of the computer, it processes set of instructions to run software programs.
*Cores and threads?
- Cores are the physical processing units in CPU that handles set of instructions when running
a program while the Threads are just logical processor that helps each core to do multitasking 
but it is not faster compared to adding additional physical core.
